By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –   Federal High Court sitting in Abuja on Monday adjourned the suit of alleged fraud of $25,000 brought before it against Senator Shehu Sani by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission. Continuing the case before Justice Inyang Ekwo on Monday, the lawyer to the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) Ekele Iheanacho after addressing the Court, introduced the prosecution witness 10 and a staff of the EFCC, Bako Aliyu. Bako Aliyu who was led in evidence by EFCC lawyer played the alleged audio conversation between Senator Shehu Sani and Alhaji Sani Dauda, proprietor of ASD motors who is the complainant.       The defence lawyer further asked the witness to confirm to the court if there was anytime through out his twenty five days detention that Senator Shehu Sani admitted collecting money to bribe anybody and his answer was negative.    By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) in a dramatic twist on Wednesday contradicted its statement that it was prosecuting the former lawmaker and human rights activist,  Shehu Sani for an alleged $25,000. At Tuesday's hearing,  the EFCC's counsel tendered documents before the Court… In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) on Monday challenged the bail application filed by Senator Shehu Sani, a former lawmaker and human rights activist who has been in detention at the Commission since 31 December 2019. In the bail application filed by… In "News" By Wandoo Sombo Abuja - Alhaji Sani Dauda, a prosecution witness, told a Federal High Court Abuja, on Monday, that Sen. Shehu Sani asked him to give N1 million each to four judges to ”help” his case.The former senator is standing trial on a two-count charge bordering on bribery and… In "News"